comment: "I can help you dig a hole" - I love Misty

Madison became so cruel after she was brought back to life. This might just be me, but think it shows that sometimes when a person is brought back to life it's not really them, but a twisted version of themself.
that's how i wake up for school every morning when my damn alarm goes off. lol

The fact that Misty didn't want to bring Madison back to life really says something about Madison. Misty knew there was something amiss about her, therefore suggested to bury her and leave it at that. But Zoe insisted, and despite Misty's better instincts, she did so anyway even though it was obviously difficult to, given Madison's rotting state. Despite this, Madison still attempts to kill Misty by having her buried alive, and let Zoe die despite having the power to bring her back to life. So yes, Madison's untimely death wasn't only well-deserved, but also long overdue.
